"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\nAnswer: 2. Somewhat likely\n\nAlthough Bond has been caught and disarmed, he has already shown his resourcefulness and agility in attempting to escape and in hiding his fountain pen. This suggests that he may still have a plan or a trick up his sleeve, making it somewhat likely that he will escape.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\nAnswer: 6. Very suspenseful\n\nThe passage is very suspenseful because Bond is in a precarious situation, having been caught by Le Chiffre and his henchmen. The use of words like \"slammed\", \"whistled\", \"crashed\", and \"barked\" creates a sense of urgency and tension. The fact that Bond is being searched and disarmed adds to the sense of danger, and the reader is left wondering how Bond will manage to escape or what will happen to him next."